Sunday, January 29, 7:30pm
Join us for a presentation by Sean Barry of New York City's Community
HIV/AIDS Mobilization Project (C.H.A.M.P.), sponsored by ACT UP Austin.
Topics will vary and include prevention and treatment policy, activist
campaigns, global policy and Bush's war on condoms. 


Sunday, February 5, 8:00pm
A show for punks featuring Buston, O Pioneers, Last Minute Fix, Hold Fast,
and Die Young.  The punk rock prices are $5


Tuesday, February 7, 7:00pm
Anti-Racist Action film night presents Invisible Revolution and A Lifetime
of Struggle.  Invisible Revolution is a documentary about the White Power
Movement and the direct action youth organization that fights it
Anti-Racist Action. This film was featured at the 2000 Sundance Film
Festival and the Human Rights Watch Film Festival 2000. The filmmaker,
Beverly Peterson was afforded unparalleled access to both groups to make
this gripping year long film.
A Lifetime of Struggle is a short film about David Gilbert,
Anti-Imperialist Political Prisoner and Prisoner of War. David is
currently serving 75 years in prison in upstate New York for his
participation in an armored car robbery in support of the Black Liberation
Army. Suggested donation is $5, and ARA will give a short presentation on
upcoming events at the conclusion of the screenings.



Friday, February 10, 7pm
MonkeyWrench Volunteer Potluck.  Do you volunteer at MonkeyWrench?  Would
you want to volunteer at MonkeyWrench?  Bring a vegetarian dish and come
by and meet the gang.

Well... you didn't wake up this morning 
Because you didn't go to bed 
You were watching the whites of your eyes turn red 
You've been reading some old letters 
You smile and think how much you've changed 
All the money in the world, Couldn't buy back those days. 
You pull back the curtains, and the sun burns into your eyes, 
You watch a plane flying across a clear blue sky. 
You could've done anything -- if you'd wanted 
And all your friends and family think that you're lucky. 
But the side of you they'll never see 
Is when you're left alone with the memories 
That hold your life together like Glue

so I have been thinking. I love the weather out right now. It makes me think. It makes me think about strange things and listening to this makes me feel happy but like there is something I need to fulfill.
I miss everyone. I want to go back to flordia and see my family. As much as I want to go east this december I may decide not to. Though I know that if I go to fla. it wont be the same. My last visit was a really good one and I am scared that if I go down there that is what I want to feel and do. But its impossible. Everythings over. It may have just been summer, I am not sure. I hate this routine. The only happiness I feel is riding the bus, having the window rolled down, feeling the wind against me, and listening to music and just dreaming. It seems so simple. But then when I get home I have things to do and different responsibilities. When my parents come home, the feeling I feel changes ubruptly. And I cant have the joy of sleeping in and waking up with my windows open and just lying there. My parents dont trust me to go on walks anymore, I rarely get out and I dont feel happy. I guess it is a summer thing, but I need to get away for a while. Its not so much that I miss flordia, I miss the people. And yes I am scared.

I hate how people fix things. They think they know whats wrong and say that they have fixed everything but wont tell me what they have fixed. They have no idea whats wrong and they dont know how I feel or what i have on my mind. They say they want to know but they dont fucking ask. I wish people understood. I wish that I didnt feel like everyone around me was so close minded. I dont want to open up to anyone anymore and I am not going to explain myself. I give them a chance to understand but they dont get anything. 
Its a great day to walk. But I know I wont be able to go. I have to finish my work first though I know its just going to put me in a bad mood. I wish everything was okay. This world is....I wish I could just go.
I look at positives so I have a reason to get out of bed in the mornings. If I didnt try to find something to live for..well hell I would be a cow!
